2118 // alignment than any other guaranteed stores, in which case we can ----
2119 // raise the alignment on the promoted store. ----
2120 Align InstAlignment = Store->getAlign(); 0
2121 bool GuaranteedToExecute = ----
2122 SafetyInfo->isGuaranteedToExecute(*UI, DT, CurLoop); 0
2123 StoreIsGuanteedToExecute |= GuaranteedToExecute; 0
2124 if (GuaranteedToExecute) { 0
2125 DereferenceableInPH = true; 0
2126 if (StoreSafety == StoreSafetyUnknown) 0
2127 StoreSafety = StoreSafe; 0
2128 Alignment = std::max(Alignment, InstAlignment); 0
2129 } ----
2130 ----
2131 // If a store dominates all exit blocks, it is safe to sink. ----
2132 // As explained above, if an exit block was executed, a dominating ----
2133 // store must have been executed at least once, so we are not ----
2134 // introducing stores on paths that did not have them. ----
2135 // Note that this only looks at explicit exit blocks. If we ever ----
2136 // start sinking stores into unwind edges (see above), this will break. ----
2137 if (StoreSafety == StoreSafetyUnknown && 0
2138 llvm::all_of(ExitBlocks, [&](BasicBlock *Exit) { 0
2139 return DT->dominates(Store->getParent(), Exit); 0
2140 })) ----
2141 StoreSafety = StoreSafe; 0
2142 ----
2143 // If the store is not guaranteed to execute, we may still get ----
2144 // deref info through it. ----
2145 if (!DereferenceableInPH) { 0
2146 DereferenceableInPH = isDereferenceableAndAlignedPointer( 0
2147 Store->getPointerOperand(), Store->getValueOperand()->getType(), ----
2148 Store->getAlign(), MDL, Preheader->getTerminator(), AC, DT, TLI); 0
2149 } ----
2150 } else ----
2151 continue; // Not a load or store. 0
2152 ----
2153 if (!AccessTy) 0
2154 AccessTy = getLoadStoreType(UI); 0
2155 else if (AccessTy != getLoadStoreType(UI)) 0
2156 return false; 0
2157 ----
2158 // Merge the AA tags. ----
2159 if (LoopUses.empty()) { 0
2160 // On the first load/store, just take its AA tags. ----
2161 AATags = UI->getAAMetadata(); 0
2162 } else if (AATags) { 0
2163 AATags = AATags.merge(UI->getAAMetadata()); 0
2164 } ----
2165 ----
2166 LoopUses.push_back(UI); 0
2167 } ----
2168 } ----
2169 ----
2170 // If we found both an unordered atomic instruction and a non-atomic memory ----
2171 // access, bail. We can't blindly promote non-atomic to atomic since we ----
2172 // might not be able to lower the result. We can't downgrade since that ----
2173 // would violate memory model. Also, align 0 is an error for atomics. ----
2174 if (SawUnorderedAtomic && SawNotAtomic) 0
2175 return false; 0
2176 ----
2177 // If we're inserting an atomic load in the preheader, we must be able to ----
2178 // lower it. We're only guaranteed to be able to lower naturally aligned ----
2179 // atomics. ----
2180 if (SawUnorderedAtomic && Alignment < MDL.getTypeStoreSize(AccessTy)) 0
2181 return false; 0
2182 ----
2183 // If we couldn't prove we can hoist the load, bail. ----
2184 if (!DereferenceableInPH) { 0
2185 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Not promoting: Not dereferenceable in preheader\n"); 0
2186 return false; 0
2187 } ----
2188 ----
2189 // We know we can hoist the load, but don't have a guaranteed store. ----
2190 // Check whether the location is writable and thread-local. If it is, then we ----
2191 // can insert stores along paths which originally didn't have them without ----
2192 // violating the memory model. ----
2193 if (StoreSafety == StoreSafetyUnknown) { 0
2194 Value *Object = getUnderlyingObject(SomePtr); 0
2195 if (isWritableObject(Object) && 0
2196 isThreadLocalObject(Object, CurLoop, DT, TTI)) 0
2197 StoreSafety = StoreSafe; 0
2198 } ----
2199 ----
2200 // If we've still failed to prove we can sink the store, hoist the load ----
2201 // only, if possible. ----
2202 if (StoreSafety != StoreSafe && !FoundLoadToPromote) 0
2203 // If we cannot hoist the load either, give up. ----
2204 return false; 0
2205 ----
2206 // Lets do the promotion! ----
2207 if (StoreSafety == StoreSafe) { 0
2208 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LICM: Promoting load/store of the value: " << *SomePtr 0
2209 << '\n'); ----
2210 ++NumLoadStorePromoted; 0
2211 } else { ----
2212 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LICM: Promoting load of the value: " << *SomePtr 0
2213 << '\n'); ----
2214 ++NumLoadPromoted; 0
2215 } ----
2216 ----
2217 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
2218 return OptimizationRemark(DEBUG_TYPE, "PromoteLoopAccessesToScalar", 0
2219 LoopUses[0]) 0
2220 << "Moving accesses to memory location out of the loop"; 0
2221 }); ----
2222 ----
2223 // Look at all the loop uses, and try to merge their locations. ----
2224 std::vector LoopUsesLocs; 0
2225 for (auto *U : LoopUses) 0
2226 LoopUsesLocs.push_back(U->getDebugLoc().get()); 0
2227 auto DL = DebugLoc(DILocation::getMergedLocations(LoopUsesLocs)); 0
2228 ----
2229 // We use the SSAUpdater interface to insert phi nodes as required. ----
2230 SmallVector NewPHIs; 0
2231 SSAUpdater SSA(&NewPHIs); 0
2232 LoopPromoter Promoter(SomePtr, LoopUses, SSA, ExitBlocks, InsertPts, ----
2233 MSSAInsertPts, PIC, MSSAU, *LI, DL, Alignment, ----
2234 SawUnorderedAtomic, AATags, *SafetyInfo, ----
2235 StoreSafety == StoreSafe); 0
2236 ----
2237 // Set up the preheader to have a definition of the value. It is the live-out ----
2238 // value from the preheader that uses in the loop will use. ----
2239 LoadInst *PreheaderLoad = nullptr; 0
2240 if (FoundLoadToPromote || !StoreIsGuanteedToExecute) { 0
2241 PreheaderLoad = 0
2242 new LoadInst(AccessTy, SomePtr, SomePtr->getName() + ".promoted", 0
2243 Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
2244 if (SawUnorderedAtomic) 0
2245 PreheaderLoad->setOrdering(AtomicOrdering::Unordered); 0
2246 PreheaderLoad->setAlignment(Alignment); 0
2247 PreheaderLoad->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
2248 if (AATags) 0
2249 PreheaderLoad->setAAMetadata(AATags); 0
2250 ----
2251 MemoryAccess *PreheaderLoadMemoryAccess = MSSAU.createMemoryAccessInBB( 0
2252 PreheaderLoad, nullptr, PreheaderLoad->getParent(), MemorySSA::End); 0
2253 MemoryUse *NewMemUse = cast(PreheaderLoadMemoryAccess); 0
2254 MSSAU.insertUse(NewMemUse, /*RenameUses=*/true); 0
2255 SSA.AddAvailableValue(Preheader, PreheaderLoad); 0
2256 } else { 0
2257 SSA.AddAvailableValue(Preheader, PoisonValue::get(AccessTy)); 0
2258 } ----
2259 ----
2260 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
2261 MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
2262 // Rewrite all the loads in the loop and remember all the definitions from ----
2263 // stores in the loop. ----
2264 Promoter.run(LoopUses); 0
2265 ----
2266 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
2267 MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
2268 // If the SSAUpdater didn't use the load in the preheader, just zap it now. ----
2269 if (PreheaderLoad && PreheaderLoad->use_empty()) 0
2270 eraseInstruction(*PreheaderLoad, *SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2271 ----
2272 return true; 0
2273 } 0
2274 ----
2275 static void foreachMemoryAccess(MemorySSA *MSSA, Loop *L, 0
2276 function_ref Fn) { ----
2277 for (const BasicBlock *BB : L->blocks()) 0
2278 if (const auto *Accesses = MSSA->getBlockAccesses(BB)) 0
2279 for (const auto &Access : *Accesses) 0
2280 if (const auto *MUD = dyn_cast(&Access)) 0
2281 Fn(MUD->getMemoryInst()); 0
2282 } 0
2283 ----
2284 // The bool indicates whether there might be reads outside the set, in which ----
2285 // case only loads may be promoted. ----
2286 static SmallVector ----
2287 collectPromotionCandidates(MemorySSA *MSSA, AliasAnalysis *AA, Loop *L) { 0
2288 BatchAAResults BatchAA(*AA); 0
2289 AliasSetTracker AST(BatchAA); 0
2290 ----
2291 auto IsPotentiallyPromotable = [L](const Instruction *I) { 0
2292 if (const auto *SI = dyn_cast(I)) 0
2293 return L->isLoopInvariant(SI->getPointerOperand()); 0
2294 if (const auto *LI = dyn_cast(I)) 0
2295 return L->isLoopInvariant(LI->getPointerOperand()); 0
2296 return false; 0
2297 }; 0
2298 ----
2299 // Populate AST with potentially promotable accesses. ----
2300 SmallPtrSet AttemptingPromotion; 0
2301 foreachMemoryAccess(MSSA, L, [&](Instruction *I) { 0
2302 if (IsPotentiallyPromotable(I)) { 0
2303 AttemptingPromotion.insert(I); 0
2304 AST.add(I); 0
2305 } ----
2306 }); 0
2307 ----
2308 // We're only interested in must-alias sets that contain a mod. ----
2309 SmallVector, 8> Sets; 0
2310 for (AliasSet &AS : AST) 0
2311 if (!AS.isForwardingAliasSet() && AS.isMod() && AS.isMustAlias()) 0
2312 Sets.push_back({&AS, false}); 0
2313 ----
2314 if (Sets.empty()) 0
2315 return {}; // Nothing to promote... 0
2316 ----
2317 // Discard any sets for which there is an aliasing non-promotable access. ----
2318 foreachMemoryAccess(MSSA, L, [&](Instruction *I) { 0
2319 if (AttemptingPromotion.contains(I)) 0
2320 return; 0
2321 ----
2322 llvm::erase_if(Sets, [&](PointerIntPair &Pair) { 0
2323 ModRefInfo MR = Pair.getPointer()->aliasesUnknownInst(I, BatchAA); 0
2324 // Cannot promote if there are writes outside the set. ----
2325 if (isModSet(MR)) 0
2326 return true; 0
2327 if (isRefSet(MR)) { 0
2328 // Remember reads outside the set. ----
2329 Pair.setInt(true); 0
2330 // If this is a mod-only set and there are reads outside the set, ----
2331 // we will not be able to promote, so bail out early. ----
2332 return !Pair.getPointer()->isRef(); 0
2333 } ----
2334 return false; 0
2335 }); ----
2336 }); ----
2337 ----
2338 SmallVector, bool>, 0> Result; 0
2339 for (auto [Set, HasReadsOutsideSet] : Sets) { 0
2340 SmallSetVector PointerMustAliases; 0
2341 for (const auto &ASI : *Set) 0
2342 PointerMustAliases.insert(ASI.getValue()); 0
2343 Result.emplace_back(std::move(PointerMustAliases), HasReadsOutsideSet); 0
2344 } 0
2345 ----
2346 return Result; 0
2347 } 0
2348 ----
2349 static bool pointerInvalidatedByLoop(MemorySSA *MSSA, MemoryUse *MU, 0
2350 Loop *CurLoop, Instruction &I, ----
2351 SinkAndHoistLICMFlags &Flags, ----
2352 bool InvariantGroup) { ----
2353 // For hoisting, use the walker to determine safety ----
2354 if (!Flags.getIsSink()) { 0
2355 // If hoisting an invariant group, we only need to check that there ----
2356 // is no store to the loaded pointer between the start of the loop, ----
2357 // and the load (since all values must be the same). ----
2358 ----
2359 // This can be checked in two conditions: ----
2360 // 1) if the memoryaccess is outside the loop ----
2361 // 2) the earliest access is at the loop header, ----
2362 // if the memory loaded is the phi node ----
2363 ----
2364 BatchAAResults BAA(MSSA->getAA()); 0
2365 MemoryAccess *Source = getClobberingMemoryAccess(*MSSA, BAA, Flags, MU); 0
2366 return !MSSA->isLiveOnEntryDef(Source) && 0
2367 CurLoop->contains(Source->getBlock()) && 0
2368 !(InvariantGroup && Source->getBlock() == CurLoop->getHeader() && isa(Source)); 0
2369 } 0
2370 ----
2371 // For sinking, we'd need to check all Defs below this use. The getClobbering ----
2372 // call will look on the backedge of the loop, but will check aliasing with ----
2373 // the instructions on the previous iteration. ----
2374 // For example: ----
2375 // for (i ... ) ----
2376 // load a[i] ( Use (LoE) ----
2377 // store a[i] ( 1 = Def (2), with 2 = Phi for the loop. ----
2378 // i++; ----
2379 // The load sees no clobbering inside the loop, as the backedge alias check ----
2380 // does phi translation, and will check aliasing against store a[i-1]. ----
2381 // However sinking the load outside the loop, below the store is incorrect. ----
2382 ----
2383 // For now, only sink if there are no Defs in the loop, and the existing ones ----
2384 // precede the use and are in the same block. ----
2385 // FIXME: Increase precision: Safe to sink if Use post dominates the Def; ----
2386 // needs PostDominatorTreeAnalysis. ----
2387 // FIXME: More precise: no Defs that alias this Use. ----
2388 if (Flags.tooManyMemoryAccesses()) 0
2389 return true; 0
2390 for (auto *BB : CurLoop->getBlocks()) 0
2391 if (pointerInvalidatedByBlock(*BB, *MSSA, *MU)) 0
2392 return true; 0
2393 // When sinking, the source block may not be part of the loop so check it. ----
2394 if (!CurLoop->contains(&I)) 0
2395 return pointerInvalidatedByBlock(*I.getParent(), *MSSA, *MU); 0
2396 ----
2397 return false; 0
2398 } ----
2399 ----
2400 bool pointerInvalidatedByBlock(BasicBlock &BB, MemorySSA &MSSA, MemoryUse &MU) { 0
2401 if (const auto *Accesses = MSSA.getBlockDefs(&BB)) 0
2402 for (const auto &MA : *Accesses) 0
2403 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast(&MA)) 0
2404 if (MU.getBlock() != MD->getBlock() || !MSSA.locallyDominates(MD, &MU)) 0
2405 return true; 0
2406 return false; 0
2407 } ----
2408 ----
2409 /// Try to simplify things like (A < INV_1 AND icmp A < INV_2) into (A < ----
2410 /// min(INV_1, INV_2)), if INV_1 and INV_2 are both loop invariants and their ----
2411 /// minimun can be computed outside of loop, and X is not a loop-invariant. ----
2412 static bool hoistMinMax(Instruction &I, Loop &L, ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, 0
2413 MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU) { ----
2414 bool Inverse = false; 0
2415 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
2416 Value *Cond1, *Cond2; ----
2417 if (match(&I, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(Cond1), m_Value(Cond2)))) { 0
2418 Inverse = true; 0
2419 } else if (match(&I, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(Cond1), m_Value(Cond2)))) { 0
2420 // Do nothing ----
2421 } else ----
2422 return false; 0
2423 ----
2424 auto MatchICmpAgainstInvariant = [&](Value *C, ICmpInst::Predicate &P, 0
2425 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS) { ----
2426 if (!match(C, m_OneUse(m_ICmp(P, m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS))))) 0
2427 return false; 0
2428 if (!LHS->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
2429 return false; 0
2430 if (!ICmpInst::isRelational(P)) 0
2431 return false; 0
2432 if (L.isLoopInvariant(LHS)) { 0
2433 std::swap(LHS, RHS); 0
2434 P = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(P); 0
2435 } ----
2436 if (L.isLoopInvariant(LHS) || !L.isLoopInvariant(RHS)) 0
2437 return false; 0
2438 if (Inverse) 0
2439 P = ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(P); 0
2440 return true; 0
2441 }; 0
2442 ICmpInst::Predicate P1, P2; ----
2443 Value *LHS1, *LHS2, *RHS1, *RHS2; ----
2444 if (!MatchICmpAgainstInvariant(Cond1, P1, LHS1, RHS1) || 0
2445 !MatchICmpAgainstInvariant(Cond2, P2, LHS2, RHS2)) 0
2446 return false; 0
2447 if (P1 != P2 || LHS1 != LHS2) 0
2448 return false; 0
2449 ----
2450 // Everything is fine, we can do the transform. ----
2451 bool UseMin = ICmpInst::isLT(P1) || ICmpInst::isLE(P1); 0
2452 assert( 0
2453 (UseMin || ICmpInst::isGT(P1) || ICmpInst::isGE(P1)) && ----
2454 "Relational predicate is either less (or equal) or greater (or equal)!"); ----
2455 Intrinsic::ID id = ICmpInst::isSigned(P1) 0
2456 ? (UseMin ? Intrinsic::smin : Intrinsic::smax) 0
2457 : (UseMin ? Intrinsic::umin : Intrinsic::umax); 0
2458 auto *Preheader = L.getLoopPreheader(); 0
2459 assert(Preheader && "Loop is not in simplify form?"); 0
2460 IRBuilder<> Builder(Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
2461 // We are about to create a new guaranteed use for RHS2 which might not exist ----
2462 // before (if it was a non-taken input of logical and/or instruction). If it ----
2463 // was poison, we need to freeze it. Note that no new use for LHS and RHS1 are ----
2464 // introduced, so they don't need this. ----
2465 if (isa(I)) 0
2466 RHS2 = Builder.CreateFreeze(RHS2, RHS2->getName() + ".fr"); 0
2467 Value *NewRHS = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic( 0
2468 id, RHS1, RHS2, nullptr, StringRef("invariant.") + 0
2469 (ICmpInst::isSigned(P1) ? "s" : "u") + 0
2470 (UseMin ? "min" : "max")); 0
2471 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&I); 0
2472 ICmpInst::Predicate P = P1; 0
2473 if (Inverse) 0
2474 P = ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(P); 0
2475 Value *NewCond = Builder.CreateICmp(P, LHS1, NewRHS); 0
2476 NewCond->takeName(&I); 0
2477 I.replaceAllUsesWith(NewCond); 0
2478 eraseInstruction(I, SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2479 eraseInstruction(*cast(Cond1), SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2480 eraseInstruction(*cast(Cond2), SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2481 return true; 0
2482 } 0
2483 ----
2484 /// Reassociate gep (gep ptr, idx1), idx2 to gep (gep ptr, idx2), idx1 if ----
2485 /// this allows hoisting the inner GEP. ----
2486 static bool hoistGEP(Instruction &I, Loop &L, ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, 0
2487 MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU, AssumptionCache *AC, ----
2488 DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2489 auto *GEP = dyn_cast(&I); 0
2490 if (!GEP) 0
2491 return false; 0
2492 ----
2493 auto *Src = dyn_cast(GEP->getPointerOperand()); 0
2494 if (!Src || !Src->hasOneUse() || !L.contains(Src)) 0
2495 return false; 0
2496 ----
2497 Value *SrcPtr = Src->getPointerOperand(); 0
2498 auto LoopInvariant = [&](Value *V) { return L.isLoopInvariant(V); }; 0
2499 if (!L.isLoopInvariant(SrcPtr) || !all_of(GEP->indices(), LoopInvariant)) 0
2500 return false; 0
2501 ----
2502 // This can only happen if !AllowSpeculation, otherwise this would already be ----
2503 // handled. ----
2504 // FIXME: Should we respect AllowSpeculation in these reassociation folds? ----
2505 // The flag exists to prevent metadata dropping, which is not relevant here. ----
2506 if (all_of(Src->indices(), LoopInvariant)) 0
2507 return false; 0
2508 ----
2509 // The swapped GEPs are inbounds if both original GEPs are inbounds ----
2510 // and the sign of the offsets is the same. For simplicity, only ----
2511 // handle both offsets being non-negative. ----
2512 const DataLayout &DL = GEP->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
2513 auto NonNegative = [&](Value *V) { 0
2514 return isKnownNonNegative(V, DL, 0, AC, GEP, DT); 0
2515 }; 0
2516 bool IsInBounds = Src->isInBounds() && GEP->isInBounds() && 0
2517 all_of(Src->indices(), NonNegative) && 0
2518 all_of(GEP->indices(), NonNegative); 0
2519 ----
2520 BasicBlock *Preheader = L.getLoopPreheader(); 0
2521 IRBuilder<> Builder(Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
2522 Value *NewSrc = Builder.CreateGEP(GEP->getSourceElementType(), SrcPtr, 0
2523 SmallVector(GEP->indices()), 0
2524 "invariant.gep", IsInBounds); ----
2525 Builder.SetInsertPoint(GEP); 0
2526 Value *NewGEP = Builder.CreateGEP(Src->getSourceElementType(), NewSrc, 0
2527 SmallVector(Src->indices()), "gep", 0
2528 IsInBounds); ----
2529 GEP->replaceAllUsesWith(NewGEP); 0
2530 eraseInstruction(*GEP, SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2531 eraseInstruction(*Src, SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2532 return true; 0
2533 } 0
2534 ----
2535 /// Try to turn things like "LV + C1 < C2" into "LV < C2 - C1". Here ----
2536 /// C1 and C2 are loop invariants and LV is a loop-variant. ----
2537 static bool hoistAdd(ICmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *VariantLHS, 0
2538 Value *InvariantRHS, ICmpInst &ICmp, Loop &L, ----
2539 ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU, ----
2540 AssumptionCache *AC, DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2541 assert(ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred) && "Not supported yet!"); 0
2542 assert(!L.isLoopInvariant(VariantLHS) && "Precondition."); 0
2543 assert(L.isLoopInvariant(InvariantRHS) && "Precondition."); 0
2544 ----
2545 // Try to represent VariantLHS as sum of invariant and variant operands. ----
2546 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
2547 Value *VariantOp, *InvariantOp; ----
2548 if (!match(VariantLHS, m_NSWAdd(m_Value(VariantOp), m_Value(InvariantOp)))) 0
2549 return false; 0
2550 ----
2551 // LHS itself is a loop-variant, try to represent it in the form: ----
2552 // "VariantOp + InvariantOp". If it is possible, then we can reassociate. ----
2553 if (L.isLoopInvariant(VariantOp)) 0
2554 std::swap(VariantOp, InvariantOp); 0
2555 if (L.isLoopInvariant(VariantOp) || !L.isLoopInvariant(InvariantOp)) 0
2556 return false; 0
2557 ----
2558 // In order to turn "LV + C1 < C2" into "LV < C2 - C1", we need to be able to ----
2559 // freely move values from left side of inequality to right side (just as in ----
2560 // normal linear arithmetics). Overflows make things much more complicated, so ----
2561 // we want to avoid this. ----
2562 auto &DL = L.getHeader()->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
2563 bool ProvedNoOverflowAfterReassociate = ----
2564 computeOverflowForSignedSub(InvariantRHS, InvariantOp, DL, AC, &ICmp, 0
2565 DT) == llvm::OverflowResult::NeverOverflows; 0
2566 if (!ProvedNoOverflowAfterReassociate) 0
2567 return false; 0
2568 auto *Preheader = L.getLoopPreheader(); 0
2569 assert(Preheader && "Loop is not in simplify form?"); 0
2570 IRBuilder<> Builder(Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
2571 Value *NewCmpOp = Builder.CreateSub(InvariantRHS, InvariantOp, "invariant.op", 0
2572 /*HasNUW*/ false, /*HasNSW*/ true); ----
2573 ICmp.setPredicate(Pred); 0
2574 ICmp.setOperand(0, VariantOp); 0
2575 ICmp.setOperand(1, NewCmpOp); 0
2576 eraseInstruction(cast(*VariantLHS), SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2577 return true; 0
2578 } 0
2579 ----
2580 /// Try to reassociate and hoist the following two patterns: ----
2581 /// LV - C1 < C2 --> LV < C1 + C2, ----
2582 /// C1 - LV < C2 --> LV > C1 - C2. ----
2583 static bool hoistSub(ICmpInst::Predicate Pred, Value *VariantLHS, 0
2584 Value *InvariantRHS, ICmpInst &ICmp, Loop &L, ----
2585 ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU, ----
2586 AssumptionCache *AC, DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2587 assert(ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred) && "Not supported yet!"); 0
2588 assert(!L.isLoopInvariant(VariantLHS) && "Precondition."); 0
2589 assert(L.isLoopInvariant(InvariantRHS) && "Precondition."); 0
2590 ----
2591 // Try to represent VariantLHS as sum of invariant and variant operands. ----
2592 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
2593 Value *VariantOp, *InvariantOp; ----
2594 if (!match(VariantLHS, m_NSWSub(m_Value(VariantOp), m_Value(InvariantOp)))) 0
2595 return false; 0
2596 ----
2597 bool VariantSubtracted = false; 0
2598 // LHS itself is a loop-variant, try to represent it in the form: ----
2599 // "VariantOp + InvariantOp". If it is possible, then we can reassociate. If ----
2600 // the variant operand goes with minus, we use a slightly different scheme. ----
2601 if (L.isLoopInvariant(VariantOp)) { 0
2602 std::swap(VariantOp, InvariantOp); 0
2603 VariantSubtracted = true; 0
2604 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred); 0
2605 } ----
2606 if (L.isLoopInvariant(VariantOp) || !L.isLoopInvariant(InvariantOp)) 0
2607 return false; 0
2608 ----
2609 // In order to turn "LV - C1 < C2" into "LV < C2 + C1", we need to be able to ----
2610 // freely move values from left side of inequality to right side (just as in ----
2611 // normal linear arithmetics). Overflows make things much more complicated, so ----
2612 // we want to avoid this. Likewise, for "C1 - LV < C2" we need to prove that ----
2613 // "C1 - C2" does not overflow. ----
2614 auto &DL = L.getHeader()->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
2615 if (VariantSubtracted) { 0
2616 // C1 - LV < C2 --> LV > C1 - C2 ----
2617 if (computeOverflowForSignedSub(InvariantOp, InvariantRHS, DL, AC, &ICmp, 0
2618 DT) != llvm::OverflowResult::NeverOverflows) 0
2619 return false; 0
2620 } else { ----
2621 // LV - C1 < C2 --> LV < C1 + C2 ----
2622 if (computeOverflowForSignedAdd(InvariantOp, InvariantRHS, DL, AC, &ICmp, 0
2623 DT) != llvm::OverflowResult::NeverOverflows) 0
2624 return false; 0
2625 } ----
2626 auto *Preheader = L.getLoopPreheader(); 0
2627 assert(Preheader && "Loop is not in simplify form?"); 0
2628 IRBuilder<> Builder(Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
2629 Value *NewCmpOp = ----
2630 VariantSubtracted ----
2631 ? Builder.CreateSub(InvariantOp, InvariantRHS, "invariant.op", 0
2632 /*HasNUW*/ false, /*HasNSW*/ true) ----
2633 : Builder.CreateAdd(InvariantOp, InvariantRHS, "invariant.op", 0
2634 /*HasNUW*/ false, /*HasNSW*/ true); 0
2635 ICmp.setPredicate(Pred); 0
2636 ICmp.setOperand(0, VariantOp); 0
2637 ICmp.setOperand(1, NewCmpOp); 0
2638 eraseInstruction(cast(*VariantLHS), SafetyInfo, MSSAU); 0
2639 return true; 0
2640 } 0
2641 ----
2642 /// Reassociate and hoist add/sub expressions. ----
2643 static bool hoistAddSub(Instruction &I, Loop &L, ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, 0
2644 MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU, AssumptionCache *AC, ----
2645 DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2646 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
2647 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred; ----
2648 Value *LHS, *RHS; ----
2649 if (!match(&I, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)))) 0
2650 return false; 0
2651 ----
2652 // TODO: Support unsigned predicates? ----
2653 if (!ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred)) 0
2654 return false; 0
2655 ----
2656 // Put variant operand to LHS position. ----
2657 if (L.isLoopInvariant(LHS)) { 0
2658 std::swap(LHS, RHS); 0
2659 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred); 0
2660 } ----
2661 // We want to delete the initial operation after reassociation, so only do it ----
2662 // if it has no other uses. ----
2663 if (L.isLoopInvariant(LHS) || !L.isLoopInvariant(RHS) || !LHS->hasOneUse()) 0
2664 return false; 0
2665 ----
2666 // TODO: We could go with smarter context, taking common dominator of all I's ----
2667 // users instead of I itself. ----
2668 if (hoistAdd(Pred, LHS, RHS, cast(I), L, SafetyInfo, MSSAU, AC, DT)) 0
2669 return true; 0
2670 ----
2671 if (hoistSub(Pred, LHS, RHS, cast(I), L, SafetyInfo, MSSAU, AC, DT)) 0
2672 return true; 0
2673 ----
2674 return false; 0
2675 } ----
2676 ----
2677 static bool hoistArithmetics(Instruction &I, Loop &L, 0
2678 ICFLoopSafetyInfo &SafetyInfo, ----
2679 MemorySSAUpdater &MSSAU, AssumptionCache *AC, ----
2680 DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2681 // Optimize complex patterns, such as (x < INV1 && x < INV2), turning them ----
2682 // into (x < min(INV1, INV2)), and hoisting the invariant part of this ----
2683 // expression out of the loop. ----
2684 if (hoistMinMax(I, L, SafetyInfo, MSSAU)) { 0
2685 ++NumHoisted; 0
2686 ++NumMinMaxHoisted; 0
2687 return true; 0
2688 } ----
2689 ----
2690 // Try to hoist GEPs by reassociation. ----
2691 if (hoistGEP(I, L, SafetyInfo, MSSAU, AC, DT)) { 0
2692 ++NumHoisted; 0
2693 ++NumGEPsHoisted; 0
2694 return true; 0
2695 } ----
2696 ----
2697 // Try to hoist add/sub's by reassociation. ----
2698 if (hoistAddSub(I, L, SafetyInfo, MSSAU, AC, DT)) { 0
2699 ++NumHoisted; 0
2700 ++NumAddSubHoisted; 0
2701 return true; 0
2702 } ----
2703 ----
2704 return false; 0
2705 } ----
2706 ----
2707 /// Little predicate that returns true if the specified basic block is in ----
2708 /// a subloop of the current one, not the current one itself. ----
2709 /// ----
2710 static bool inSubLoop(BasicBlock *BB, Loop *CurLoop, LoopInfo *LI) { 0
2711 assert(CurLoop->contains(BB) && "Only valid if BB is IN the loop"); 0
2712 return LI->getLoopFor(BB) != CurLoop; 0
2713 } ----
